news.title: Days after techie’s death, Noida authority identifies 65 spots lacking safety
news.para: Following a fatal accident, Noida Authority identified 65 road safety black spots and will issue notices to developers for construction site safety.  Repairs and improvements, including addressing drainage issues and recruiting sanitary inspectors, are prioritized to prevent future tragedies.

news.title: Hyderabad: One lakh property owners evaded ₹100 crore tax, finds GHMC survey
news.para: A GHMC GIS survey identified over one lakh property owners who evaded over Rs 100 crore in taxes through under-assessment. This occurred between 2020-2023 when self-assessment was permitted, leading to undeclared commercial use and altered plinth areas. The corporation is now issuing notices to defaulters.

news.title: Noida: HC upholds UP-RERA relief for Gaur City Centre shop buyers
news.para: The Allahabad High Court dismissed four appeals by Gaursons Hi-Tech Infrastructure, refusing to condone delays in shop-buyer disputes at Gaur City Centre. The court cited the developer's lack of diligence and unsatisfactory reasons for delays, upholding orders from UP-Rera and REAT. This decision allows buyers to pursue execution of Rera orders.

news.title: Rising debt & sops may prompt Maharashtra government to increase RR rate this April
news.para: Property buyers in Pune may face higher costs soon. Government officials are considering a rise in Ready Reckoner rates from April. This move aims to address a growing revenue deficit and fund welfare schemes. Developers oppose the hike, citing strong property market performance. The decision will impact stamp duty and registration charges.

news.title: Delhi village bodies seek relief from house tax, urban regulations
news.para: Village leaders from Delhi presented their concerns to the chairperson of the MCD Standing Committee. They voiced strong opposition to the house tax and urban regulations that heavily impact rural communities. The representatives argued that these financial strains are too much for villagers to bear and sought exemptions from MCD building bye-laws.

news.title: United Kingdom to cap ground rents in property overhaul
news.para: Britain is capping ground rents at 250 pounds annually. This reform targets leasehold properties, easing financial burdens for millions. The system, rooted in medieval law, will see permitted ground rents reduced to a nominal amount after 40 years. New leasehold flats will also be banned.

news.title: Maharashtra cabinet approves Metro project to link Mumbai and Navi Mumbai airports
news.para: A new Metro line will connect Mumbai and Navi Mumbai international airports. The 35-km corridor will feature 20 stations. The project, costing over Rs 22,000 crore, aims for completion within three years of approvals. Land acquisition and approvals are targeted within six months.

news.title: Vanke gets approval for more bond repayment deferrals as China is seen stepping in to avert immediate default
news.para: China Vanke has secured approval from bondholders to postpone some debt payments. This move provides the property developer with crucial breathing room. Beijing's intervention played a role in Vanke's sweetened proposals. The company faces significant debt and is central to China's property sector crisis.

news.title: PropEquity partners with Department of Land Economy at Cambridge University to offer real estate course
news.para: PE Analytics and the University of Cambridge are collaborating to enhance educational offerings and develop skills for the Indian real estate sector. The partnership will also explore research, including AI-driven predictive models.

news.title: Asian Paints' net profit dips 4.83% in Q3 FY26
news.para: Asian Paints announced its financial results for the quarter ending December 31, 2025. The company's net consolidated profit saw a decrease of 4.83 percent. Despite this, total income grew by 3.86 percent.

news.title: WeWork India posts net profit of ₹16.78 crore in Q3 FY26
news.para: WeWork India  reported a net profit of over ₹16 crore for the quarter ending December 31, 2025. This marks a turnaround from a loss in the same period last year. Total income also saw a substantial rise.

news.title: Raymond Realty posts net profit of ₹66.79 crore in Q3 FY26
news.para: Raymond Realty's profit after tax surged to ₹66.79 crore in the quarter ending December 31, 2025. This marks an increase from ₹3.01 crore in the same period last year. The company's total income also saw a jump to ₹765.97 crore.

news.title: HERE Solutions leases 2.1 lakh sq ft in Navi Mumbai’s Airoli
news.para: HERE Technologies India has made headlines by clinching a substantial office lease of over 2.1 lakh sq ft at the prime location of Mindspace Airoli West. This 10+ year contract reflects the thriving market activity within Navi Mumbai's business hubs.

news.title: India's luxury housing market may cool down in FY27, feel 56% of HNIs in ISIR survey
news.para: Luxury home demand and prices might decrease in India's major cities next fiscal year. A survey of wealthy individuals shows over half expect a market moderation. Despite this, most remain optimistic about India's economic growth.

news.title: Delhi government working towards improving living standards of slum residents: CM
news.para: Delhi Chief Minister Rekha Gupta celebrated Republic Day with slum dwellers,  inaugurating development projects valued at Rs 327 crore. The government has allocated Rs 144 crore for various projects, aiming to enhance living standards and provide essential amenities for residents.

news.title: Lorazzo raises ₹5 crore in seed funding led by Sprout Venture Partners, India Quotient
news.para: Home improvement startup Lorazzo secured ₹5 crore in seed funding. The investment, led by Sprout Venture Partners and India Quotient, will boost product development and expand distribution.

news.title: Pune stamp duty collections cross ₹7,100 crore in 2025: Knight Frank
news.para: Pune's property landscape reached a milestone in 2025, recording an exceptional stamp duty revenue of over ₹7,100 crore. Despite a slight reduction in property registrations, the surge in sales of higher-value homes drove growth in revenue. There is a strong demand for larger, premium properties among buyers.

news.title: Housing sales dips 14% in top seven cities: Report
news.para: In 2025, the housing market saw a significant decline in sales volume, yet the total value of property transactions soared. This suggests a transformative shift in buyer preferences, with an increasing appetite for upscale residences and more spacious living options.
